Gospel artists say the public broadcaster and the Southern African Music Rights Organisation are not supporting local gospel artists The group hosted a Gospel Indaba in Pretoria over the genre being sidelined. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some local gospel artists say they're being sidelined and are calling for more airplay. The Gospel Indaba Organisers met in Pretoria to discuss a way forward. They say government isn't doing enough and is planning to protest. Gospel artists say the public broadcaster and the Southern African Music Rights Organisation are not supporting them. All gospel artists are being urged to speak up and voice their concerns. * eNCA's Nqobile Madlala reports.